126 static void rangeProcDSP_WaitEDMAComplete
127 (
128  EDMA_Handle edmaHandle,
129  uint8_t chId
130 )
131 {
132  volatile bool isTransferDone = false;
133  do {
134  if (EDMA_isTransferComplete(edmaHandle,
135  (uint8_t) chId,
136  (bool *)&isTransferDone) != EDMA_NO_ERROR)
137  {
138  }
139  } while (isTransferDone == false);

157 static int32_t rangeProcDSP_ConfigDataInEDMA
158 (
159  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj,
160  DPU_RangeProcDSP_HW_Resources *hwRes
161 )
162 {
163  int32_t retVal;
164  rangeProc_dpParams *dpParams;
165  DPEDMA_syncACfg syncACfg;
166 
167  dpParams = &rangeProcObj->DPParams;
168 
169  /* Copy data from ADCbuffer to internal adcbufIn scratch buffer
170  Assumes the input data is in non-interleaved mode
171  */
172  syncACfg.aCount = dpParams->numAdcSamples * BYTES_PER_SAMP_1D;
173  syncACfg.bCount =MAX(dpParams->numRxAntennas / 2U, 1U) * dpParams->numChirpsPerChirpEvent;
174  syncACfg.srcBIdx = rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset * 2U ;
175  syncACfg.dstBIdx = 0U;
176 
177  /* PING configuration */
178  syncACfg.srcAddress = (uint32_t)rangeProcObj->ADCdataBuf;
179  syncACfg.destAddress = (uint32_t)rangeProcObj->adcDataIn;
180 
181  retVal = DPEDMA_configSyncA_singleFrame(hwRes->edmaCfg.edmaHandle,
182  &hwRes->edmaCfg.dataInPing,
183  NULL, /* no Chaining */
184  &syncACfg,
185  false,
186  true,
187  true,
188  NULL,
189  NULL);
190  if (retVal < 0)
191  {
192  goto exit;
193  }
194 
195  /* PONG src/dest address */
196  syncACfg.srcAddress = (uint32_t)rangeProcObj->ADCdataBuf + rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset;
197  syncACfg.destAddress = (uint32_t)&rangeProcObj->adcDataIn[dpParams->numRangeBins];
198 
199  retVal = DPEDMA_configSyncA_singleFrame(hwRes->edmaCfg.edmaHandle,
200  &hwRes->edmaCfg.dataInPong,
201  NULL, /* no Chaining */
202  &syncACfg,
203  false,
204  true,
205  true,
206  NULL,
207  NULL);
208  if (retVal < 0)
209  {
210  goto exit;
211  }
212 exit:
213  return(retVal);
214 }

231 static int32_t rangeProcDSP_ConfigDataOutEDMA
232 (
233  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj,
234  DPU_RangeProcDSP_HW_Resources *hwRes
235 )
236 {
237  int32_t retVal;
238  uint16_t samplesPerChirp, aCount;
239  uint16_t oneD_destinationCindex;
240  uint8_t *oneD_destinationPongAddress;
241  DPEDMA_syncABCfg syncABCfg;
242  rangeProc_dpParams *dpParams;
243  DPU_RangeProcDSP_EDMAConfig *edmaCfg;
244 
245  edmaCfg = &hwRes->edmaCfg;
246  dpParams = &rangeProcObj->DPParams;
247 
248  /*****************************************************
249  * EDMA configuration for storing 1d fft output to L3.
250  * It copies all Rx antennas of the chirp per trigger event.
251  *****************************************************/
252  samplesPerChirp = dpParams->numRangeBins * dpParams->numRxAntennas;
253  aCount = samplesPerChirp * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
254 
255  if ((dpParams->numTxAntennas == 2U) || (dpParams->numTxAntennas == 3U))
256  {
257  oneD_destinationCindex = (int16_t)aCount;
258 
259  /* Calculation address for 2 TxAnt. 3 txAnt , the address is calculated at runtime */
260  oneD_destinationPongAddress = (uint8_t *)(&rangeProcObj->radarCubebuf[samplesPerChirp * dpParams->numDopplerChirps]);
261  }
262  else if (dpParams->numTxAntennas == 1U)
263  {
264  oneD_destinationCindex = (int16_t)(aCount * 2U);
265  oneD_destinationPongAddress = (uint8_t *)(&rangeProcObj->radarCubebuf[samplesPerChirp]);
266  }
267  else
268  {
269  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
270  goto exit;
271  }
272 
273  /* Ping/Pong common configuration */
274  syncABCfg.aCount = dpParams->numRangeBins * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
275  syncABCfg.bCount = dpParams->numRxAntennas;
276  syncABCfg.cCount = dpParams->numChirpsPerFrame / 2U; /*bCount */
277  syncABCfg.srcBIdx = dpParams->numRangeBins * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
278  syncABCfg.srcCIdx = 0;
279  syncABCfg.dstBIdx = dpParams->numRangeBins * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
280  syncABCfg.dstCIdx = oneD_destinationCindex;
281 
282  syncABCfg.srcAddress = (uint32_t)rangeProcObj->fftOut1D;
283  syncABCfg.destAddress= (uint32_t)rangeProcObj->radarCubebuf;
284 
285  /* Ping - Copies from ping FFT output (even chirp indices) to L3 */
286  retVal = DPEDMA_configSyncAB (edmaCfg->edmaHandle,
287  &edmaCfg->dataOutPing,
288  NULL,
289  &syncABCfg,
290  false,
291  true,
292  true,
293  NULL,
294  NULL
295  );
296  if (retVal < 0)
297  {
298  goto exit;
299  }
300 
301  /* Pong - copies from pong FFT output (odd chirp indices) to L3 */
302  syncABCfg.srcAddress = (uint32_t)&rangeProcObj->fftOut1D[samplesPerChirp];
303  syncABCfg.destAddress= (uint32_t)oneD_destinationPongAddress;
304 
305  retVal = DPEDMA_configSyncAB (edmaCfg->edmaHandle,
306  &edmaCfg->dataOutPong,
307  NULL,
308  &syncABCfg,
309  false,
310  true,
311  true,
312  NULL,
313  NULL
314  );
315 
316 exit:
317  return(retVal);
318 }

336 static int32_t rangeProcDSP_dcRangeSignatureCompensation_init
337 (
338  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj,
339  DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg *calibDcRangeSigCfg,
340  uint8_t resetMeanBuffer
341 )
342 {
343  int32_t retVal = 0;
344  uint32_t meanbufSize;
345 
346  meanbufSize = DPU_RANGEPROC_SIGNATURE_COMP_MAX_BIN_SIZE * rangeProcObj->DPParams.numVirtualAntennas
347  * sizeof(cmplx32ImRe_t);
348 
349  /* Validate DC revomal configuraiton */
350  if(calibDcRangeSigCfg->enabled)
351  {
352  if( (rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMean == (cmplx32ImRe_t*)NULL) ||
353  (rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMeanBufSize < meanbufSize))
354  {
355  /* Check DC range average buffer pointer */
356  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
357  goto exit;
358  }
359  else
360  {
361  if(resetMeanBuffer == 1U)
362  {
363  /* Initialize memory */
364  memset((void *)rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMean, 0, meanbufSize);
365  rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr = 0;
366  }
367  rangeProcObj->calibDcNumLog2AvgChirps = mathUtils_floorLog2(calibDcRangeSigCfg->numAvgChirps);
368  }
369  }
370  else
371  {
372  /* Feature is disabled , nothing needs to done here */
373  }
374 
375 exit:
376  return (retVal);
377 }

405 static void rangeProcDSP_dcRangeSignatureCompensation
406 (
407  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj,
408  DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg *calibDcCfg,
409  uint8_t chirpPingPongId,
410  uint8_t txIdx
411 )
412 {
413  rangeProc_dpParams *params;
414  uint32_t rxAntIdx, binIdx;
415  uint32_t ind;
416  int32_t chirpPingPongOffs;
417  int32_t chirpPingPongSize;
418 
419  params = &rangeProcObj->DPParams;
420  chirpPingPongSize = params->numRxAntennas * (calibDcCfg->positiveBinIdx - calibDcCfg->negativeBinIdx + 1);
421 
422  chirpPingPongOffs = txIdx * chirpPingPongSize;
423 
424  /* Calibration */
425  if (rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr < (calibDcCfg->numAvgChirps * params->numTxAntennas))
426  {
427  /* Accumulate */
428  ind = 0;
429  for (rxAntIdx = 0; rxAntIdx < params->numRxAntennas; rxAntIdx++)
430  {
431  uint32_t chirpInOffs = chirpPingPongId * (params->numRxAntennas * params->numRangeBins) +
432  (params->numRangeBins * rxAntIdx);
433  int64_t *meanPtr = (int64_t *) &rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMean[chirpPingPongOffs];
434  uint32_t *fftPtr = (uint32_t *) &rangeProcObj->fftOut1D[chirpInOffs];
435  int64_t meanBin;
436  uint32_t fftBin;
437  int32_t Re, Im;
438  for (binIdx = 0; binIdx <= calibDcCfg->positiveBinIdx; binIdx++)
439  {
440  meanBin = _amem8(&meanPtr[ind]);
441  fftBin = _amem4(&fftPtr[binIdx]);
442  Im = _loll(meanBin) + _ext(fftBin, 0, 16);
443  Re = _hill(meanBin) + _ext(fftBin, 16, 16);
444  _amem8(&meanPtr[ind]) = _itoll(Re, Im);
445  ind++;
446  }
447 
448  chirpInOffs = chirpPingPongId * (params->numRxAntennas * params->numRangeBins) +
449  (params->numRangeBins * rxAntIdx) + params->numRangeBins + calibDcCfg->negativeBinIdx;
450  fftPtr = (uint32_t *) &rangeProcObj->fftOut1D[chirpInOffs];
451  for (binIdx = 0; binIdx < -calibDcCfg->negativeBinIdx; binIdx++)
452  {
453  meanBin = _amem8(&meanPtr[ind]);
454  fftBin = _amem4(&fftPtr[binIdx]);
455  Im = _loll(meanBin) + _ext(fftBin, 0, 16);
456  Re = _hill(meanBin) + _ext(fftBin, 16, 16);
457  _amem8(&meanPtr[ind]) = _itoll(Re, Im);
458  ind++;
459  }
460  }
461 
462  if (rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr == (calibDcCfg->numAvgChirps * params->numTxAntennas - 1))
463  {
464  /* Divide */
465  int64_t *meanPtr = (int64_t *) rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMean;
466  int32_t Re, Im;
467  int64_t meanBin;
468  int32_t divShift = mathUtils_floorLog2(calibDcCfg->numAvgChirps);
469  for (ind = 0; ind < (params->numTxAntennas * chirpPingPongSize); ind++)
470  {
471  meanBin = _amem8(&meanPtr[ind]);
472  Im = _sshvr(_loll(meanBin), divShift);
473  Re = _sshvr(_hill(meanBin), divShift);
474  _amem8(&meanPtr[ind]) = _itoll(Re, Im);
475  }
476  }
477  }
478  else
479  {
480  /* fftOut1D -= dcRangeSigMean */
481  ind = 0;
482  for (rxAntIdx = 0; rxAntIdx < params->numRxAntennas; rxAntIdx++)
483  {
484  uint32_t chirpInOffs = chirpPingPongId * (params->numRxAntennas * params->numRangeBins) +
485  (params->numRangeBins * rxAntIdx);
486  int64_t *meanPtr = (int64_t *) &rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMean[chirpPingPongOffs];
487  uint32_t *fftPtr = (uint32_t *) &rangeProcObj->fftOut1D[chirpInOffs];
488  int64_t meanBin;
489  uint32_t fftBin;
490  int32_t Re, Im;
491  for (binIdx = 0; binIdx <= calibDcCfg->positiveBinIdx; binIdx++)
492  {
493  meanBin = _amem8(&meanPtr[ind]);
494  fftBin = _amem4(&fftPtr[binIdx]);
495  Im = _ext(fftBin, 0, 16) - _loll(meanBin);
496  Re = _ext(fftBin, 16, 16) - _hill(meanBin);
497  _amem4(&fftPtr[binIdx]) = _pack2(Im, Re);
498  ind++;
499  }
500 
501  chirpInOffs = chirpPingPongId * (params->numRxAntennas * params->numRangeBins) +
502  (params->numRangeBins * rxAntIdx) + params->numRangeBins + calibDcCfg->negativeBinIdx;
503  fftPtr = (uint32_t *) &rangeProcObj->fftOut1D[chirpInOffs];
504  for (binIdx = 0; binIdx < -calibDcCfg->negativeBinIdx; binIdx++)
505  {
506  meanBin = _amem8(&meanPtr[ind]);
507  fftBin = _amem4(&fftPtr[binIdx]);
508  Im = _ext(fftBin, 0, 16) - _loll(meanBin);
509  Re = _ext(fftBin, 16, 16) - _hill(meanBin);
510  _amem4(&fftPtr[binIdx]) = _pack2(Im, Re);
511  ind++;
512  }
513  }
514  }
515 }

532 static int32_t rangeProcDSP_ParseConfig
533 (
534  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj,
535  DPU_RangeProcDSP_Config *pConfigIn
536 )
537 {
538  int32_t retVal = 0;
539  rangeProc_dpParams *params;
540  DPU_RangeProcDSP_StaticConfig *pStaticCfg;
541  DPU_RangeProcDSP_HW_Resources *pHwRes;
542 
543  /* Get configuration pointers */
544  pStaticCfg = &pConfigIn->staticCfg;
545  pHwRes = &pConfigIn->hwRes;
546  params = &rangeProcObj->DPParams;
547 
548  /* Save datapath parameters */
549  params->numTxAntennas = pStaticCfg->numTxAntennas;
550  params->numRxAntennas = pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.numRxAntennas;
551  params->numVirtualAntennas = pStaticCfg->numVirtualAntennas;
552  params->numChirpsPerChirpEvent = pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.numChirpsPerChirpEvent;
553  params->numAdcSamples = pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.numAdcSamples;
554  params->numRangeBins = pStaticCfg->numRangeBins;
555  params->numChirpsPerFrame = pStaticCfg->numChirpsPerFrame;
556  params->numDopplerChirps = pStaticCfg->numChirpsPerFrame/pStaticCfg->numTxAntennas;
557 
558  /* Save EDMA Handle */
559  rangeProcObj->edmaHandle = pHwRes->edmaCfg.edmaHandle;
560 
561  /* Save interface buffers */
562  rangeProcObj->ADCdataBuf = (cmplx16ImRe_t *)pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.data;
563  rangeProcObj->radarCubebuf = (cmplx16ImRe_t *)pHwRes->radarCube.data;
564 
565  /* Save Scratch buffers */
566  rangeProcObj->fftOut1D = pHwRes->fftOut1D;
567  rangeProcObj->adcDataIn = pHwRes->adcDataIn;
568  rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMean = pHwRes->dcRangeSigMean;
569  rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMeanBufSize = pHwRes->dcRangeSigMeanSize;
570 
571  /* Scratch windowing & twiddle buffers */
572  rangeProcObj->twiddle16x16 = pHwRes->twiddle16x16;
573  rangeProcObj->window = pHwRes->window;
574 
575  if(params->numRxAntennas > 1)
576  {
577  /* For rangeProc DPU needs rx channel has same offset from one channel to the next channel
578  Use first two channel offset to calculate the BIdx for EDMA
579  */
580  rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset = pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.rxChanOffset[1] -
581  pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.rxChanOffset[0];
582 
583  /* rxChanOffset should be 16 bytes aligned and should be big enough to hold numAdcSamples */
584  if (rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset < rangeProcObj->DPParams.numAdcSamples * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t) ||
585  (rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset & 0xF != 0))
586  {
587  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
588  goto exit;
589  }
590  }
591 
592  /* Prepare Ping/Pong EDMA data in/out channels */
593  rangeProcObj->dataInChan[0] = pHwRes->edmaCfg.dataInPing.channel;
594  rangeProcObj->dataInChan[1] = pHwRes->edmaCfg.dataInPong.channel;
595  rangeProcObj->dataOutChan[0] = pHwRes->edmaCfg.dataOutPing.channel;
596  rangeProcObj->dataOutChan[1] = pHwRes->edmaCfg.dataOutPong.channel;
597 
598  /* Calculation used at runtime */
599  rangeProcObj->numSamplePerChirp = params->numRangeBins * params->numRxAntennas ;
600  rangeProcObj->numSamplePerTx = params->numDopplerChirps *rangeProcObj->numSamplePerChirp;
601 
602 exit:
603  return(retVal);
604 }

623 DPU_RangeProcDSP_Handle DPU_RangeProcDSP_init
624 (
625  int32_t* errCode
626 )
627 {
628  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj;
629 
630  rangeProcObj = MemoryP_ctrlAlloc(sizeof(rangeProcDSPObj), 0);
631  if(rangeProcObj == NULL)
632  {
633  *errCode = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_ENOMEM;
634  return NULL;
635  }
636 
637  /* Initialize memory */
638  memset((void *)rangeProcObj, 0, sizeof(rangeProcDSPObj));
639 
640  return ((DPU_RangeProcDSP_Handle)rangeProcObj);
641 }

661 int32_t DPU_RangeProcDSP_config
662 (
663  DPU_RangeProcDSP_Handle handle,
664  DPU_RangeProcDSP_Config* pConfig
665 )
666 {
667  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj;
668  DPU_RangeProcDSP_StaticConfig *pStaticCfg;
669  DPU_RangeProcDSP_HW_Resources *pHwRes;
670  int32_t retVal = 0;
671 
672  rangeProcObj = (rangeProcDSPObj *)handle;
673  if(rangeProcObj == NULL)
674  {
675  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
676  goto exit;
677  }
678 
679  pStaticCfg = &pConfig->staticCfg;
680  pHwRes = &pConfig->hwRes;
681 
682 #if DEBUG_CHECK_PARAMS
683  /* Validate params */
684  if(!pConfig->hwRes.edmaCfg.edmaHandle ||
685  !pHwRes->radarCube.data ||
686  !pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.data||
687  !pHwRes->adcDataIn ||
688  !pHwRes->fftOut1D ||
689  !pHwRes->window ||
690  !pHwRes->twiddle16x16 ||
691  !pHwRes->dcRangeSigMean
692  )
693  {
694  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
695  goto exit;
696  }
697 
698  if(rangeProcObj->inProgress == true)
699  {
700  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINPROGRESS;
701  goto exit;
702  }
703 
704  /* Parameter check: validate Adc data interface configuration
705  Support:
706  - Complex 16bit ADC data in IMRE format
707  - Non-interleaved mode
708  */
709  if( (pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.dataFmt != DPIF_DATAFORMAT_COMPLEX16_IMRE) ||
710  (pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.interleave != DPIF_RXCHAN_NON_INTERLEAVE_MODE) )
711  {
712  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
713  goto exit;
714  }
715 
716  /* Validate dp radarCube interface */
717  if (pConfig->hwRes.radarCube.datafmt != DPIF_RADARCUBE_FORMAT_1)
718  {
719  /* Only one format is supported */
720  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
721  goto exit;
722  }
723 
724  /* Validate windowing configuraiton */
725  if(pHwRes->windowSize != (pStaticCfg->ADCBufData.dataProperty.numAdcSamples *sizeof(int16_t) / 2U))
726  {
727  /* Only one format is supported */
728  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
729  goto exit;
730  }
731 #endif
732  /* Save hardware resources */
733  memcpy((void *)&rangeProcObj->calibDcRangeSigCfg, (void *)pConfig->dynCfg.calibDcRangeSigCfg, sizeof(DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg));
734 
735  retVal = rangeProcDSP_ParseConfig(rangeProcObj, pConfig);
736  if(retVal < 0)
737  {
738  goto exit;
739  }
740 
741  /* Generate twiddle factors for 1D FFT. This is one time */
742  mmwavelib_gen_twiddle_fft16x16_imre_sa((short *)rangeProcObj->twiddle16x16, pStaticCfg->numRangeBins);
743 
744  /* Configure EDMA */
745  retVal = rangeProcDSP_ConfigDataInEDMA(rangeProcObj, &pConfig->hwRes);
746  if(retVal < 0)
747  {
748  goto exit;
749  }
750  retVal = rangeProcDSP_ConfigDataOutEDMA(rangeProcObj, &pConfig->hwRes);
751  if(retVal < 0)
752  {
753  goto exit;
754  }
755 
756  /* DC calibration and compensation init */
757  retVal = rangeProcDSP_dcRangeSignatureCompensation_init(rangeProcObj,
758  pConfig->dynCfg.calibDcRangeSigCfg,
759  pStaticCfg->resetDcRangeSigMeanBuffer);
760  if (retVal < 0)
761  {
762  goto exit;
763  }
764 
765  rangeProcObj->chirpCount = 0;
766  rangeProcObj->inProgress = false;
767 exit:
768  return retVal;
769 }
770 
789 int32_t DPU_RangeProcDSP_process
790 (
791  DPU_RangeProcDSP_Handle handle,
792  DPU_RangeProc_OutParams *outParams
793 )
794 {
795  rangeProc_dpParams *DPParams;
796  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj;
797  EDMA_Handle edmaHandle;
798  uint32_t rxChanId;
799  volatile uint32_t startTime;
800  volatile uint32_t startTime1;
801  uint32_t waitingTime;
802  uint32_t outChannel;
803  uint16_t chirpIndex;
804  uint8_t chirpPingPongId;
805  int32_t retVal = 0;
806  uint32_t totalChirpIndex;
807 
808  rangeProcObj = (rangeProcDSPObj *)handle;
809  if(rangeProcObj == NULL)
810  {
811  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
812  goto exit;
813  }
814 
815  if(rangeProcObj->inProgress == true)
816  {
817  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINPROGRESS;
818  goto exit;
819  }
820  else
821  {
822  rangeProcObj->inProgress = true;
823  }
824 
825  DPParams = &rangeProcObj->DPParams;
826  edmaHandle = rangeProcObj->edmaHandle;
827 
828  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
829  waitingTime = 0;
830 
831  outParams->endOfChirp = false;
832 
833  /*
834  Process chirp data per loop, loops for numChirpsPerChirpEvent
835  */
836  for (chirpIndex = 0; chirpIndex < DPParams->numChirpsPerChirpEvent; chirpIndex++)
837  {
838  uint32_t dataInAddr[2];
839  uint32_t numAdcSampleAligned;
840  cmplx16ImRe_t *adcBufPongOffset;
841 
842  /*********************************
843  * Prepare for the FFT
844  *********************************/
845  numAdcSampleAligned = (DPParams->numAdcSamples + 3U)/4U * 4U;
846  adcBufPongOffset = (cmplx16ImRe_t *)((uint32_t)rangeProcObj->ADCdataBuf + rangeProcObj->rxChanOffset);
847 
848  dataInAddr[0] = (uint32_t)&rangeProcObj->ADCdataBuf[chirpIndex * numAdcSampleAligned];
849  dataInAddr[1] = (uint32_t)&adcBufPongOffset[chirpIndex * numAdcSampleAligned];
850 
851  /* Set Ping source Address */
852  EDMA_setSourceAddress(edmaHandle, rangeProcObj->dataInChan[0],
853  (uint32_t) SOC_translateAddress(dataInAddr[0], SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_TO_EDMA, NULL));
854 
855  /* Set Pong source Address */
856  EDMA_setSourceAddress(edmaHandle, rangeProcObj->dataInChan[1],
857  (uint32_t) SOC_translateAddress(dataInAddr[1], SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_TO_EDMA, NULL));
858 
859  /* Kick off DMA to fetch data from ADC buffer for first channel */
860  EDMA_startDmaTransfer(edmaHandle, rangeProcObj->dataInChan[0]);
861 
862  chirpPingPongId = pingPongId(rangeProcObj->chirpCount);
863  /* 1d fft for first antenna, followed by kicking off the DMA of fft output */
864  for (rxChanId = 0; rxChanId < DPParams->numRxAntennas; rxChanId++)
865  {
866  int16_t *fftSrcAddr;
867  int16_t *fftDestAddr;
868  uint8_t inChannel;
869 
870  /*********************************
871  * Data Input
872  *********************************/
873  inChannel = rangeProcObj->dataInChan[pingPongId(rxChanId)];
874 
875  /* Get the src/dest Address for FFT operation */
876  fftSrcAddr = (int16_t*)&rangeProcObj->adcDataIn[pingPongId(rxChanId) * DPParams->numRangeBins];
877  fftDestAddr = (int16_t*)&rangeProcObj->fftOut1D[chirpPingPongId * rangeProcObj->numSamplePerChirp +
878  (DPParams->numRangeBins * rxChanId)];
879 
880  if(rxChanId<DPParams->numRxAntennas -1U)
881  {
882  /* Kick off DMA to fetch data from ADC buffer for the next channel */
883  EDMA_startDmaTransfer(edmaHandle, rangeProcObj->dataInChan[pingPongId(rxChanId + 1)]);
884  }
885 
886  /* Verify if DMA has completed for current antenna */
887  startTime1 = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
888  rangeProcDSP_WaitEDMAComplete ( edmaHandle, inChannel);
889  waitingTime += (Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime1);
890 
891  /*********************************
892  * Data Processing
893  *********************************/
894 
895  /* Only support even length of windowing */
896  mmwavelib_windowing16x16_evenlen(
897  (int16_t *) fftSrcAddr,
898  (int16_t *) rangeProcObj->window,
899  DPParams->numAdcSamples);
900 
901  /* Zero out padding region */
902  memset((void *)&rangeProcObj->adcDataIn[pingPongId(rxChanId) * DPParams->numRangeBins + DPParams->numAdcSamples],
903  0 , (DPParams->numRangeBins - DPParams->numAdcSamples) * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t));
904 
905  /* 16bit FFT in imre format */
906  DSP_fft16x16_imre(
907  (int16_t *) rangeProcObj->twiddle16x16,
908  DPParams->numRangeBins,
909  (int16_t *)fftSrcAddr,
910  (int16_t *) fftDestAddr);
911 
912  }
913 
914  /*********************************
915  * DC removal processing
916  *********************************/
917 
918  if(rangeProcObj->calibDcRangeSigCfg.enabled)
919  {
920  int32_t chirpPingPongSize;
921 
922  chirpPingPongSize = DPParams->numRxAntennas * (rangeProcObj->calibDcRangeSigCfg.positiveBinIdx -
923  rangeProcObj->calibDcRangeSigCfg.negativeBinIdx + 1);
924 
925  if (rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr == 0)
926  {
927  memset(rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigMean, 0, DPParams->numTxAntennas * chirpPingPongSize * sizeof(cmplx32ImRe_t));
928  }
929 
930  rangeProcDSP_dcRangeSignatureCompensation(rangeProcObj,
931  &rangeProcObj->calibDcRangeSigCfg,
932  chirpPingPongId,
933  rangeProcObj->chirpCount%DPParams->numTxAntennas);
934 
935  rangeProcObj->dcRangeSigCalibCntr++;
936  }
937 
938  /*********************************
939  * Data Output
940  *********************************/
941  outChannel = rangeProcObj->dataOutChan[chirpPingPongId];
942 
943  /* For non TDM case, when chirpBytes is >= 16384, the destinationBindex in
944  EDMA will be twice of this which is negative jump, so need to set the
945  destination address in this situation.
946  e.g if numRangeBins = 1024, numRxAntennas = 4 then destinationBindex becomes -32768 */
947  if ((DPParams->numTxAntennas == 1U) && (rangeProcObj->numSamplePerChirp * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t) >= (uint32_t)16384U) )
948  {
949  uint32_t radarCubeAddr;
950 
951  radarCubeAddr = (uint32_t)(rangeProcObj->radarCubebuf + rangeProcObj->chirpCount * rangeProcObj->numSamplePerChirp);
952  EDMA_setDestinationAddress(edmaHandle, outChannel,
953  (uint32_t)SOC_translateAddress((radarCubeAddr), SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_TO_EDMA, NULL));
954  }
955  /* Limitation of EDMA index settings, manually set the destination Address */
956  else if ((DPParams->numTxAntennas == 2U) && (rangeProcObj->numSamplePerChirp * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t) >= (uint32_t)32768) ||
957  (DPParams->numTxAntennas == 3U))
958  {
959  uint32_t radarCubeAddr;
960  uint8_t numTxAnt;
961 
962  totalChirpIndex = rangeProcObj->chirpCount;
963  numTxAnt = DPParams->numTxAntennas;
964 
965  radarCubeAddr = (uint32_t)(rangeProcObj->radarCubebuf + rangeProcObj->numSamplePerTx *(totalChirpIndex % numTxAnt) +
966  (totalChirpIndex/numTxAnt)*rangeProcObj->numSamplePerChirp);
967  EDMA_setDestinationAddress(edmaHandle, outChannel,
968  (uint32_t)SOC_translateAddress((radarCubeAddr), SOC_TranslateAddr_Dir_TO_EDMA, NULL));
969  }
970  else
971  {
972  /* Other cases does not need manually set the destination address */
973  }
974 
975  if(rangeProcObj->chirpCount > 1U)
976  {
977  startTime1 = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
978  rangeProcDSP_WaitEDMAComplete ( edmaHandle, outChannel);
979  waitingTime += (Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime1);
980  }
981 
982  EDMA_startDmaTransfer(edmaHandle, outChannel);
983 
984  /* Increment chirp count */
985  rangeProcObj->chirpCount++;
986 
987  /* Last chirp , wait until EDMA is completed */
988  if(rangeProcObj->chirpCount == DPParams->numChirpsPerFrame)
989  {
990  /* Wait until last tansfer is done */
991  rangeProcDSP_WaitEDMAComplete ( edmaHandle, outChannel);
992  rangeProcObj->chirpCount = 0;
993  outParams->endOfChirp = true;
994  }
995 
996  rangeProcObj->numProcess++;
997  }
998 
999  /* Update outParams */
1000  outParams->stats.processingTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime - waitingTime;
1001  outParams->stats.waitTime = waitingTime;
1002 
1003  rangeProcObj->inProgress = false;
1004 
1005 exit:
1006  return retVal;
1007 }
1008 
1028 int32_t DPU_RangeProcDSP_control
1029 (
1030  DPU_RangeProcDSP_Handle handle,
1031  DPU_RangeProcDSP_Cmd cmd,
1032  void* arg,
1033  uint32_t argSize
1034 )
1035 {
1036  int32_t retVal = 0;
1037  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj;
1038 
1039  /* Get rangeProc data object */
1040  rangeProcObj = (rangeProcDSPObj *)handle;
1041 
1042  /* Sanity check */
1043  if (rangeProcObj == NULL)
1044  {
1045  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
1046  goto exit;
1047  }
1048 
1049  /* Check if control() is called during processing time */
1050  if(rangeProcObj->inProgress == true)
1051  {
1052  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINPROGRESS;
1053  goto exit;
1054  }
1055 
1056  /* Control command handling */
1057  switch(cmd)
1058  {
1059  case DPU_RangeProcDSP_Cmd_dcRangeCfg:
1060  {
1061  DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg *calibDc;
1062 
1063  if((argSize != sizeof(DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg)) ||
1064  (arg == NULL))
1065  {
1066  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
1067  goto exit;
1068  }
1069  else
1070  {
1071  calibDc = (DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg *)arg;
1072 
1073  if(memcmp((void *)&rangeProcObj->calibDcRangeSigCfg,
1074  (void *)calibDc, sizeof(DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg)) == 0)
1075  {
1076  /* NO configuration change, nothing needs to be done here */
1077  }
1078  else
1079  {
1080  retVal = rangeProcDSP_dcRangeSignatureCompensation_init(rangeProcObj, calibDc, 1U);
1081  if(retVal < 0)
1082  {
1083  goto exit;
1084  }
1085  else
1086  {
1087  /* Save configuration */
1088  memcpy((void *)&rangeProcObj->calibDcRangeSigCfg, (void *)arg, argSize);
1089  }
1090  }
1091  }
1092  }
1093  break;
1094 
1095  default:
1096  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_ECMD;
1097  break;
1098  }
1099 exit:
1100  return (retVal);
1101 }
1102 
1120 int32_t DPU_RangeProcDSP_deinit(DPU_RangeProcDSP_Handle handle)
1121 {
1122  rangeProcDSPObj *rangeProcObj;
1123  int32_t retVal = 0;
1124 
1125  /* Sanity Check */
1126  rangeProcObj = (rangeProcDSPObj *)handle;
1127  if(rangeProcObj == NULL)
1128  {
1129  retVal = DPU_RANGEPROCDSP_EINVAL;
1130  goto exit;
1131  }
1132  else
1133  {
1134  /* Free memory */
1135  MemoryP_ctrlFree(handle, sizeof(rangeProcDSPObj));
1136  }
1137 exit:
1138  return (retVal);
1139 }
